27/05/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The third regional conference on war crimes began Tuesday (May26th) on the island of Brijuni.
Hague tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz is attending the forum along with Vincent Degert, head of the European Commission delegation to Croatia, and Clint Williamson, US ambassador-at-large for war crimes issues.
State attorneys and prosecutors of countries in the region are holding closed-door discussions on war crimes proceedings.
The conference aims to strengthen co-operation among regional war crimes prosecutors.
(HRT, Javno, HINA, Jutarnji, RTS - 26/05/09)
